    $translate['en']['dev_sec_hardware_title'] = "Hardware development";
    $translate['en']['dev_sec_hardware_1'] = "The first prototype of a computer was being developed during 1939-1942  in the USA.";
    $translate['en']['dev_sec_hardware_2'] = "In 1939-1941 a Z3 computer is built by Konrad Zuse. Some people believe it was a machine preceding its own era, similar to contemporary computers.";
    $translate['en']['dev_sec_hardware_3'] = "In 1943 Colossus was built - it was the first computer constructed in the UK. It was used to decrypt German army’s communication.";
    $translate['en']['dev_sec_hardware_4'] = "ENIAC - built during 1943-1945 in the University of Pennsylvania, USA.
It did not have RAM and it was initially coded by switching cable plugs, later by using perforated cards.
ENIAC characteristics:
- weight: 27 tones;
- 18 000 electronic lamps;
- surface: 140 m<sup>2</sup>
- mainly used for military purposes (ballistic calculations, calculations related to nuclear weaponry)";
    $translate['en']['dev_sec_hardware_5'] = "1960s - the production of IBM 360 series computers";
    $translate['en']['dev_sec_hardware_6'] = "In 1967 Steve Wozniak and Steve Jobs released the first widely available PC - the Apple I.";
    $translate['en']['dev_sec_hardware_7'] = "In 1970 the first Polish computer (K-202) is built by using integrated circuitry. It was constructed by the Eng. Jacek Karpiński’s team. It is said that the Polish computer was faster than first IMB PCs. 30 computers have been produced. However, the invention was not appreciated by the communist government and after its eventual failure, Mr. Karpiński ran his own pig breeding.";
    $translate['en']['dev_sec_hardware_8'] = "In 1979 a new type of computers debuted - the laptops. They were primarily used by the NASA for their space shuttle programme.";
    $translate['en']['dev_sec_hardware_9'] = "On August 1981 the MS-DOS system was introduced.";
    $translate['en']['dev_sec_hardware_10'] = "On August 1982 Commodore 64 had its premiere, during that time it was believed to be a total best-seller among all PCs (17 million products sold)";
    $translate['en']['dev_sec_hardware_11'] = "1984 was the year of Macintosh’s debut. It was the first widely sold PC with graphic interface (GUI).";
    $translate['en']['dev_sec_hardware_12'] = "In 1985 Microsoft implemented Windows 1.0, which was a graphic overlay for the MS-DOS system.";
    $translate['en']['dev_sec_hardware_13'] = "In 1995 Windows 95 had its premiere, which turned out to be a huge success for the Microsoft (1 million sold copies in 4 days). 
During the 1990s the Office bundle and highly valued Internet Explorer 1 had their own debuts.";
    $translate['en']['dev_sec_hardware_14'] = "In 2001 Xbox had its debut and becomes a strong opposition to PlayStation2. Also, Windows XP was introduced, 
being more stable and efficient in comparison to its older versions.";
    $translate['en']['dev_sec_hardware_15'] = "2009 is the year of the Windows 7 premiere. The beta version of the OS was previously tested by a couple of million users.
In that version touch screens support became available to users.";
    $translate['en']['dev_sec_hardware_16'] = "In 2012 Microsoft presented 2 in 1 devices (devices functioning both as laptops and tablets), classified as the surface products line.";
    $translate['en']['dev_sec_hardware_17'] = "The newest OS from Microsoft MS, Windows 10, is available since September 2014.";
//section software
    $translate['en']['dev_sec_networks_title'] = "Network development";
    $translate['en']['dev_sec_network_1'] = "In 1960 the first project about networking was described by J. Licklider";
    $translate['en']['dev_sec_network_2'] = "In 1962 Paul Baran published a work consisting of 12 volumes about durable, dispersed data communication networks, capable of surviving the upcoming war. It was feared that soon after the WW2 a WW3 may broke out, where usage of nuclear weapons would be on a daily basis.";
    $translate['en']['dev_sec_network_3'] = "On 29th October 1969 on the University of California a new type of network was being developed - the ARPANET. The network was supposed not to have its own central point, which could be used for controlling the connected computers. The entire project was coordinated by ARPA, the organisation responsible for coordinating research for the military";
    $translate['en']['dev_sec_network_4'] = "ARPANET did not possess any reliable mechanism for identifying other devices, which was a huge obstacle in the further development of this technology. At the beginning of 1970s a TCP/IP protocol was being created.
[(Transmission Control Protocol/Internet Protocol)]";
    $translate['en']['dev_sec_network_5'] = "In 1971 engineer Ray Tomlinson wrote the first programme, which allowed to send messages between computers.
";
    $translate['en']['dev_sec_network_6'] = "In 1979 Kevin MacKenzie was the first man to use an emoticon. During the same year the USENET was created. It used to be a network connecting two universities, which had a number of newsgroups.";
    $translate['en']['dev_sec_network_7'] = "In 1982 the Usenet i Arpanet were connected to each other.";
    $translate['en']['dev_sec_network_8'] = "On 1st January 1983 the ARPANET network changed its NCP protocol (Network Control Protocol) to TCP/IP. In 1983 DNS system was created.
(a relation between IP addresses and domain names).";
    $translate['en']['dev_sec_network_9'] = "In 1990 the ARPANET network was shut down. Its role was claimed by many other networks, which used to be a part of the Internet. On December 1990 the first website was created by Tim Berners-Lee. 
On the same year Archie FTP browser also had its premiere.";
    $translate['en']['dev_sec_network_10'] = "In 1991 National Science Foundation has cancelled the prohibition determining the usage of networks in commercial purposes (advertising, selling). Since that moment the Internet was used in the aforementioned manner.";
    $translate['en']['dev_sec_network_11'] = "On June 1993 Moisac was created. It was the first graphical WWW browser. Another, very popular browser was a bit later released Netspace Navigator, which initially used to dominate the market  (it took about 90 % of the market). Later on the market was claimed by the creation of Microsoft - the Internet Explorer.";
    $translate['en']['dev_sec_network_12'] = "In 1995 AltaVista was introduced, the first search engine on the web. It used to index the website by the frequency of a searched word occurrence.";
    $translate['en']['dev_sec_network_13'] = "In 1996 the first instant messenger is introduced - ICQ, as well as the CSS coding language. Also, a new search engine was developed on the Stanford University. It used to search for the given search terms not by the amount of available links leading to the website but by their quality.";
    $translate['en']['dev_sec_network_14'] = "1997 - premiere of the PHP i JavaScript";
    $translate['en']['dev_sec_network_15'] = "7th September 1998 - Google was founded.";
    $translate['en']['dev_sec_network_16'] = "In 2000 a RSS channel was created.";
    $translate['en']['dev_sec_network_17'] = "4th February 2004 - Facebook was founded.";
